ouis as St Louis Comptroller from 1973 to 1977 From 1991 to 1995 Bass provided his expertise and administrative abilities while working as a staff member for committees of the U S House of Representatives in Washington D C He worked as a staff director and senior executive for the House Subcommittee on Libraries and Memorials with oversight responsibilities for the Smithsonian Institution the Kennedy Performing Arts Center and the Division of Congressional Research the think tank for the U S Congress Bass was consultant to the U S Office of Education and the Department of Labor He also was a staff member of the Oversight Committee U S House Committee on Administration responsible for House operations investigations staffing and public policy Bass has served as an educator counselor and administrator in the St Louis public schools and has been a member of the faculty and staff of the University of Missouri St Louis and the University of Missouri Kansas City He has been a guest professor at Harris Stowe State College and is active in numerous professional and civic organizations Bass served in the U S Navy He received a B A in business and school administration from Lincoln University and M A in counseling and school administration from Washington University and has taken postgraduate courses in the St Louis area Bass resides in St Louis and has one daughter top back to top gif Diane M Bourisaw Diana M Bourisaw Imperial is currently working on two national initiatives to develop schools throughout the country One is a program funded by Bill and Melinda Gates to develop 12 small model high schools The other is a faith based initiative to develop schools in urban areas to aid poor and minority children She has held a number of positions in K 12 education including superintendent principal assistant principal consultant dean of students teacher and school board member She is involved in various community organizations and has been honored for her service in K 12 education She holds a B S B S E and M A from Northeast Missouri State University and a Ph D in educational administration from Iowa State University top back to top gif Marie Carmichael Marie Carmichael has served three terms as chair of the Coordinating Board She holds a BA degree in English from Pittsburg State University Kansas and an MA degree in English from the University of Arkansas Fayetteville where she was awarded a graduate fellowship She has taught English at the college level University of Arkansas and at the high school level Springfield Public Schools During the past few years Mrs Carmichael has been actively involved in promoting collaboration between higher education and K 12 She served on the state s first K 16 Coalition which focused on improving student achievement in mathematics through the joint efforts of K 12 and higher education She also served on the K 16 Task Force which addressed the issue of eliminating achievement gaps Additionally she serves as chair of the Missouri Advanced Placement Advisory Board In Springfield where she resides Mrs Carmichael serves on the Community Advisory Board to the College of Education at SMSU and is a member of the Greenwood Laboratory School Advisory Board She and her husband Joe have two children She is a realtor and part owner of a real estate development company top back to top gif Dudley Grove Dudley Grove is a former elementary school teacher with a long history of volunteer service and 20 years of experience consulting and training non profit organizations She is a member of the Metropolitan Association for Philanthropy Board the Whitaker Foundation Board and the Chancellor s Council for the University of Missouri St Louis and is chair of the Employment Committee of the Urban League She was a Danforth Leadership Program fellow and holds an M B A from the University of Missouri St Louis Ms Grove currently serves as Secretary of the Coordinating Board for Higher Education top back to top gif Lowell Kruse Governor Holden nominated Lowell Kruse of St Joseph to the Coordinating Board for Higher Education on January 3 2003 Mr Kruse has served as President and CEO of Heartland Health for the last 18 years In addition he serves on the Board of Directors for the Excellence in Missouri Foundation and sits on the board of the Area Health Education Center AHEC Mr Kruse earned a bachelor s degree from Augustana College in Sioux Falls South Dakota and a master s degree from the University of Minnesota Mr Kruse currently serves as Vice Chair of the Coordinating Board for Higher Education top back to top gif Robert L Langdon Robert L Langdon is a partner of Langdon Emison Kuhlman Evans LLC in Lexington practicing in the field of products liability He has been in practice since his admittance to the Missouri Bar in 1973 He has been a board member executive board member and past president of the Missouri Association of Trial Attorneys He also is a member of the Association of Trial Lawyers of America as well as its Board of Directors Langdon received his Certificate of Trial Advocacy from the National Board of Advocacy in May 1985 and is an associate member of the American Board of Trial Advocates In addition to the Missouri Bar he is a member and past president of the Lafayette County Bar Association and a member of the Kansas City Bar Association Langdon received a B S in education from the University of Missouri in 1970 and a J D from the University of Missouri Columbia in 1972 top back to top gif Kathryn Swan is President and owner of JCS TEL LINK a small wireless communications company located in Cape Girardeau Missouri with offices in Anna and Chester Illinois The company provides two way radio cellular paging wireless connectivity satellite telephone and auto sound products as well as related services Kathy has earned an Associate of Arts and Bachelor of Science degrees in Nursing from Southeast Missouri State University and has taken additional coursework in finance management and accounting In addition Kathy has been employed in various nursing positions at Southeast Missouri State University and Saint Francis Medical Center Kathy is involved in numerous professional organizations as well as community groups Professionally she is Chairman Emeritus of the Board of the Great Lakes MSS Motorola Service Station Association a member of the National MSS Association National Federation of Independent Business Missouri Chamber of Commerce Leadership Missouri Alumni Association and former Vice Chairman of the Cape Girardeau Chamber of Commerce Her company received the Small Business of the Year Award in 1997 from the Chamber of Commerce Kathy is seriously committed to community involvement having served in a membership or leadership role in over 20 organizations and committees Currently she is a board member of the following United Way Saint Francis Medical Center Foundation American Cancer Society and the Zonta Club of Cape Girardeau In addition she serves as a member of Governor Holden s Business Education Roundtable Vision 2020 Community Relations Council the Education Council Administrative Committee of the Missouri Chamber of Commerce the Leadership Council of NFIB Missouri and the Status of Women Service Committee Chairman of District 7 Zonta Club In April 2003 Governor Holden appointed Kathy to serve on the Missouri Coordinating Board for Higher Education Formerly she served as a member of the Board of Education for the Cape Girardeau School District and was active in regional and state school board association activities In addition she is a past president of the Zonta Club of Cape Girardeau Area and formerly served as the Service Committee Chairman as well as a committee member of numerous committees Kathy has received many awards Vision 2000 Award of Distinction in 1998 2000 and 2002 Zonta Woman of Achievement Award Girl Scouts 2002 Women s Impact Award Community Counseling Center Outstanding Achievement Award Dr A M Estes Award from the 